Real estate firm VAAL has signed an agreement for the management of Divine Residences on Riverside Drive, Nairobi. VAAL Real Estate will manage the residences in partnership with Valor Hospitality Partners and CityBlue Hotels. “It is my pleasure to announce to you that VAAL Real Estate has signed the International Hotel Management Agreement for the Divine Suites LTD with Valor Hospitality Partners and CityBlue Hotels,” said VAAL Real Estate CEO Majeed Saad. Divine Residences by CityBlue on Riverside Drive is a development by VAAL Real Estate. It consists 252 units services apartments for both short- and long-term guests. “The Interior Design of the project is Classic Contemporary with a touch of Eclectic. It has been developed by HBA, the World’s leading Hospitality Design Firm,” said Laura Salzmann, Marketing Manager at VAAL Real Estate. “After analyzing the Kenyan and especially the Nairobi Hospitality Market, HBA came up with a design that will attract international and local business travelers alike.” Video Of The Day: Former sports CS Hassan Wario convicted over Rio games scam